<paragraph id="8BEA4143FFFBFA4FD9FF39E9FDE06C6F" blockId="8.[189,1399,450,512]" lastBlockId="9.[189,1399,267,367]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<collectionCode id="ED44D986FFFBFA4ED9FF39E9FF676CDD" box="[189,209,450,476]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
rheophytically adapted sister species closely allied to 
<taxonomicName id="4C553AC0FFFBFA4EDA1939E8FB756CDD" authority="Jack (Jack 1822)" authorityName="Jack (Jack" authorityYear="1822" box="[859,1219,450,476]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sublobata">
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFFBFA4EDA1939E8FC446CDD" box="[859,1010,450,476]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B. sublobata</emphasis>
Jack (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC43CB2FFFBFA4EDD7D39E9FB0C6CDD" author="Jack W." box="[1087,1210,450,476]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 96" refId="ref18405" refString="Jack W. 1822. Descriptions of Malayan plants. Malayan Miscellanies 2 (7): 1 - 96." type="journal article" year="1822">Jack 1822</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs in its smaller size (&lt;
<quantity id="4CADECA6FFFBFA4EDB4C39CEFDEE6CFE" box="[526,600,485,511]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="cm" value="20.0">20 cm</quantity>
high, not 
<quantity id="4CADECA6FFFBFA4EDB9139CEFCFF6CFE" box="[723,841,485,511]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="cm" value="25.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="20.0">20–30 cm</quantity>
high) and its smaller, narrower leaves (8–15 × 
<quantity id="4CADECA6FFFAFA4FD9FF3920FEF36C27" box="[189,325,267,294]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="cm" value="3.5" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="1.5">1.5–5.5 cm</quantity>
, not 
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFFAFA4FD8C03927FE206C24" box="[386,406,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">c.</emphasis>
12 × 
<quantity id="4CADECA6FFFAFA4FD8A23920FD996C27" box="[480,559,267,294]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="cm" value="12.0">12 cm</quantity>
). Other distinctive characters are the petioles being triangular in cross section, and the cuneate lamina with up to 3 apical lobes. See also the diagnosis for 
<taxonomicName id="4C553AC0FFFAFA4FDDCC391AFA9E6C4B" authorityName="M. Hughes" authorityYear="2015" box="[1166,1320,304,330]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lilliputana">
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFFAFA4FDDCC391AFA9E6C4B" box="[1166,1320,304,330]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">B. lilliputana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
below for a comparison with that species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF2A11CBFFFBFA4ED9FF3F86FD6E6AEA" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3805823" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3805823" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3805823/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" startId="8.[189,232,1965,1991]" targetBox="[189,1398,586,1923]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph id="8BEA4143FFFBFA4ED9FF3F86FD6E6AEA" blockId="8.[189,1399,1965,2027]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFFBFA4ED9FF3F86FEBF6AC6" bold="true" box="[189,265,1965,1991]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 2.</emphasis>
Map of Sumatra showing the full known species distributions based on collection localities. Each point may represent more than one collection.
</paragraph>
</caption>
