<paragraph id="8BEA4143FFFAFA4FD9FF39ECFBF46CE0" blockId="9.[189,1090,455,482]" box="[189,1090,455,482]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
The epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFFAFA4FDB3639ECFD776CE0" box="[628,705,455,481]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">fluvius</emphasis>
(river) and means “of the river”.
</paragraph>
