<subSubSection id="C34F12C8FFF8FA4DD9FF3AA7FE616E1D" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="multiple">
<paragraph id="8BEA4143FFF8FA4DD9FF3AA7FE586FA7" blockId="11.[189,494,652,678]" box="[189,494,652,678]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<heading id="D0A2F62FFFF8FA4DD9FF3AA7FE586FA7" bold="true" box="[189,494,652,678]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFF8FA4DD9FF3AA7FE586FA7" bold="true" box="[189,494,652,678]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA4143FFF8FA4DD9FF3A90FE616E1D" blockId="11.[189,1399,699,796]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Only known from two collections from neighbouring streams near Sungai 
<collectingRegion id="49918FA1FFF8FA4DDD133A90FB146FD4" box="[1105,1186,699,725]" country="Malaysia" name="Pulau Pinang" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Pinang</collectingRegion>
in 
<collectingRegion id="49918FA1FFF8FA4DDD8D3A90FAC16FD4" box="[1231,1399,699,725]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Barat" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">West Sumatra</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation id="136E5DC6FFF8FA4DD9843AF5FEA76FF9" box="[198,273,734,760]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,232,1965,1991]" captionTargetBox="[207,1380,627,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[207,1380,626,1924]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 4. Map of Sumatra showing the full known species distributions based on collection localities. Each point may represent more than one collection." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3805829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3805829/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C553AC0FFF8FA4DD86B3AF4FE1F6FF9" authorityName="M. Hughes" authorityYear="2015" box="[297,425,734,760]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fluvialis">
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFF8FA4DD86B3AF4FE1F6FF9" box="[297,425,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">B. fluvialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows on moss covered rocks at the side of and emerging from streams running down the mountainside.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34F12C8FFF8FA4DD9FF3B68FEA46EF6" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8BEA4143FFF8FA4DD9FF3B68FE036E5F" blockId="11.[189,437,835,862]" box="[189,437,835,862]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<heading id="D0A2F62FFFF8FA4DD9FF3B68FE036E5F" bold="true" box="[189,437,835,862]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFF8FA4DD9FF3B68FE036E5F" bold="true" box="[189,437,835,862]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Conservation status</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA4143FFF8FA4DD9FF3B59FEA46EF6" blockId="11.[189,1399,882,1015]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
The forest habitat of the 
<typeStatus id="54EEFFE1FFF8FA4DD89E3B58FDB96E8C" box="[476,527,883,909]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">type</typeStatus>
locality seems to be well managed and under some community protection. However the lack of a formally gazetted protected area and the potential for landslides to encroach the streamside habitat means 
<taxonomicName id="4C553AC0FFF8FA4DD8AD3B91FDDB6ED2" authorityName="M. Hughes" authorityYear="2015" box="[495,621,953,979]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fluvialis">
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFF8FA4DD8AD3B91FDDB6ED2" box="[495,621,953,979]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">B. fluvialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be considered Vulnerable under criterion VUD2 of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC43CB2FFF8FA4DDC6D3B92FEBD6EF6" author="IUCN" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref18379" refString="IUCN 2012. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. Second Edition. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK." type="book" year="2012">IUCN (2012)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
